When hitting a database from a php program, you generally must check for errors.

So, replace

    $query-&gt;execute();

with

    $queryStatus = $query-&gt;execute();
    if (!$queryStatus) {
        die &quot;Query &quot; . $sql . &quot; failed: &quot; $query-&gt;error;
    }

And, you probably will be wise to get rid of `error_reporting(0);`. Don&#39;t even consider putting it back until your code is completely debugged.

